g.text: The ML System's Health Check: Monitoring in Production

text.font-family: Excalifont, Xiaolai, sans-serif, Segoe UI Emoji

g.text: Traditional software fails by crashing. ML systems can fail silently by becoming gradually less accurate over time.

text.font-family: Excalifont, Xiaolai, sans-serif, Segoe UI Emoji

g.text: We are monitoring for drifta change in the relationship between our input data and the outcomes we want to predict.

text.font-family: Excalifont, Xiaolai, sans-serif, Segoe UI Emoji

g.text: This drift makes our model's learned patterns obsolete.

text.font-family: Excalifont, Xiaolai, sans-serif, Segoe UI Emoji

g.text: Data drift occurs when the live data the model sees in production no longer resembles the data it was trained on

g.text: The statistical properties of the live data the model sees in production no longer match the properties of the data it was trained on. In

g.text: Silent model failure. Your system is running, but its predictions become progressively less accurate because its learned "rules" are now outdated.

text.font-family: Excalifont, Xiaolai, sans-serif, Segoe UI Emoji

g.text: The joint probability distribution of features (X) and labels (y) in production is no longer the same as it was in training.

text.font-family: Excalifont, Xiaolai, sans-serif, Segoe UI Emoji
Excalifont, Xiaolai, sans-serif, Segoe UI Emoji

g.text: The input data distribution is different, but the relationship between inputs and outputs is the same.

text.font-family: Excalifont, Xiaolai, sans-serif, Segoe UI Emoji

g.text: A loan model trained on older customers is now used for younger customers. The rules of risk are the same, but the population is new.

text.font-family: Excalifont, Xiaolai, sans-serif, Segoe UI Emoji
Excalifont, Xiaolai, sans-serif, Segoe UI Emoji
Excalifont, Xiaolai, sans-serif, Segoe UI Emoji

g.text: The relationship between inputs and outputs changes. The same input now means something different.

text.font-family: Excalifont, Xiaolai, sans-serif, Segoe UI Emoji

g.text: Before a pandemic, has_home_office=false had little impact on house price. After the pandemic, the same feature has_home_office=false

text.font-family: Excalifont, Xiaolai, sans-serif, Segoe UI Emoji

g.text: means the house is worth significantly less.

text.font-family: Excalifont, Xiaolai, sans-serif, Segoe UI Emoji
Excalifont, Xiaolai, sans-serif, Segoe UI Emoji

g.text: The overall frequency of the different classes (labels) changes in the real world.

text.font-family: Excalifont, Xiaolai, sans-serif, Segoe UI Emoji

g.text: A spam filter was trained when spam was 10% of all email. Now, a new phishing attack makes spam 40% of all email. The model,

text.font-family: Excalifont, Xiaolai, sans-serif, Segoe UI Emoji

g.text: expecting spam to be rare, may fail to adapt and miss many new threats.

text.font-family: Excalifont, Xiaolai, sans-serif, Segoe UI Emoji
Excalifont, Xiaolai, sans-serif, Segoe UI Emoji

g.text: Models degrade in production due to data drift. We must have a process to update them with new data.

text.font-family: Excalifont, Xiaolai, sans-serif, Segoe UI Emoji

g.text: Most organizations evolve their retraining capabilities through four stages of maturity, moving from manual and reactive

text.font-family: Excalifont, Xiaolai, sans-serif, Segoe UI Emoji
Excalifont, Xiaolai, sans-serif, Segoe UI Emoji
Excalifont, Xiaolai, sans-serif, Segoe UI Emoji
Excalifont, Xiaolai, sans-serif, Segoe UI Emoji

g.text: Models are retrained from scratch by an engineer running a script. This is only done when performance has noticeably dropped.

text.font-family: Excalifont, Xiaolai, sans-serif, Segoe UI Emoji
Excalifont, Xiaolai, sans-serif, Segoe UI Emoji

g.text: The retraining process is automated and runs on a fixed schedule (e.g., daily, weekly). The model is still rebuilt from scratch each time.

text.font-family: Excalifont, Xiaolai, sans-serif, Segoe UI Emoji
Excalifont, Xiaolai, sans-serif, Segoe UI Emoji

g.text: The pipeline is now "stateful." It doesn't retrain from scratch but fine-tunes the existing model on new data since the last update.

text.font-family: Excalifont, Xiaolai, sans-serif, Segoe UI Emoji
Excalifont, Xiaolai, sans-serif, Segoe UI Emoji

g.text: The highest level of maturity. Retraining is no longer on a fixed schedule. It is automatically triggered by monitoring systems when

text.font-family: Excalifont, Xiaolai, sans-serif, Segoe UI Emoji

g.text: they detect significant data drift or a drop in model performance.

text.font-family: Excalifont, Xiaolai, sans-serif, Segoe UI Emoji

g.text: Testing in Production: Safely Deploying New Models

text.font-family: Excalifont, Xiaolai, sans-serif, Segoe UI Emoji

g.text: Offline evaluation on a static test set isn't enough. It can't predict how a model will perform on live, unseen data or how its

text.font-family: Excalifont, Xiaolai, sans-serif, Segoe UI Emoji
Excalifont, Xiaolai, sans-serif, Segoe UI Emoji

g.text: Test your new "challenger" model against the old "champion" model using live production traffic. This is the ultimate test of a model's

text.font-family: Excalifont, Xiaolai, sans-serif, Segoe UI Emoji
Excalifont, Xiaolai, sans-serif, Segoe UI Emoji

g.text: Never deploy a new model to 100% of users at once. Use a phased approach to measure its impact and ensure it's a true

Excalifont, Xiaolai, sans-serif, Segoe UI Emoji

g.text: The core question of an A/B test: Is the observed improvement in the challenger model (B) real, or just random chance?
